# Pulse Studio - AI Assistant Rules

## General Principles
- **Maintain Modularity:** Keep UI components in `src/components/` and core logic in `src/lib/`.
- **Type Safety:** Always use TypeScript interfaces and types defined in `src/types/index.ts`.
- **State Management:** Use React hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`) and custom hooks in `src/hooks/` for state persistence.
- **Styling:** Use Tailwind CSS utility classes for all styling. Follow the established design patterns.
- **AI Integration:** Use the `callLLM` and `generatePodcastAudio` services in `src/lib/podcastService.ts` for all AI interactions.

## Component Guidelines
- **Functional Components:** Use functional components with React hooks.
- **Props Interfaces:** Always define an interface for component props.
- **Lucide Icons:** Use `lucide-react` for all icons.
- **Motion Animations:** Use `motion` from `motion/react` for animations and transitions.

## Logic & Services
- **Prompt Management:** Centralize all AI prompts in `src/lib/prompts.ts`.
- **Utility Functions:** Keep general-purpose utility functions in `src/lib/utils.ts`.
- **Constants:** Use `src/lib/constants.ts` for all application-wide constants and default values.

## Automation & Integration
- **Frontend-Only:** Maintain the application as a pure frontend solution for easy deployment and use with mobile automation tools.
- **LocalStorage Persistence:** Ensure all user settings and topics are persisted in `localStorage`.
- **PWA Support:** Follow PWA best practices for offline support and mobile installation.

## Communication
- **Clear Summary:** When making changes, provide a concise summary of the modifications.
- **Action Over Talk:** Prioritize implementation over lengthy explanations.
- **Respect Intent:** Do not revert user changes or functional improvements.
